This paper discusses the use of electromagnetic side-channel analysis (EM-SCA) for digital forensic investigations of IoT devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper focuses on detecting cryptographic algorithms and malicious modifications. The paper also involves hardware and software analysis, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering), respectively. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact on human-computer interaction and privacy, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
